[b]Market Structure Pivot Map [WavesUnchained][/b]

[b]What it does[/b]
A clean structural location map. It plots higher-timeframe pivot levels (Daily / Weekly / Monthly), the Central Pivot Range (CPR), previous high/low, the current-day open, and range projections — then tells you where price sits relative to that structure. It is a location tool, not a buy/sell signal generator: it answers "where are we", not "trade now".

[b]Levels[/b]
[list]
[*]Classic or Fibonacci pivots: P, R1–R4, S1–S4
[*]Central Pivot Range (P / TC / BC) with a width regime — Narrow / Normal / Wide vs daily ATR
[*]Previous high/low and current-day open
[*]Range projections (0.25 / 0.50 / 1.00) off Day Open, Previous Close, or Pivot, using ADR, previous-day range, or ATR
[/list]

[b]Confluence[/b]
[list]
[*]All drawn levels are clustered across timeframes
[*]A zone is highlighted where several levels stack within a configurable ATR distance
[*]Cross-timeframe overlaps (e.g. Daily R1 on Weekly P) are where structure matters most
[/list]

[b]Context readout[/b]
[list]
[*]Nearest support and resistance with distance measured in ATR
[*]CPR location (above / inside / below) and width regime
[*]Bullish / Bearish / Neutral context based on close and day open relative to the CPR
[/list]

[b]Modes[/b]
[list]
[*]Auto — selects the pivot timeframe from the chart period
[*]Manual — overlay any combination of Daily / Weekly / Monthly
[/list]

Pivot levels are read from the previous completed period and do not repaint during the current period.

